--TEST IT--

7-Go to Product and create state to hold the products

const [product, setProduct] = useState({})
const [error, setError] = useState(false)

8-create a method and run it in useEffect.

9-// take props in the Product component

useEffect(() => {
  const productId = props.match.params.productId;
  loadSingleProduct(productId);
}, []);


10-create the loadSingleProduct method above the useEffect


// create read method to get a single product from the api

const loadSingleProduct = (productId) => {
  read(productId).then((data) => {
    if (data.error) {
      setError(data.error);
    } else {
      setProduct(data);
    }
  });
};

11-Go into the Layout (still on Product) and add heading:

<h2 className="mb-4">Single Product</h2>
<div className="row">
    {JSON.stringify(product)}
</div>

